# Web + Mobile Sync Policy

This repo has **web** (`web/`), **mobile** (`mobile/app/`), and **shared packages** (`packages/`).

## When to update BOTH web and mobile

| Change type | Shared location | Mobile mirror |
|-------------|-----------------|---------------|
| Portal labels/keys | `packages/shared-constants/src/portals.ts` | Auto via import; check `LoginScreen.tsx` |
| Roles/permissions | `packages/shared-constants/src/roles.ts` | Auto via import |
| Auth / API clients | `packages/shared-services/` | `mobile/app/src/adapters/` + shared-services |
| Portal screen logic | `web/src/modules/{portal}/` | `mobile/app/src/portals/{portal}/` |

## Web-only (no mobile update required)

Tailwind layout, Sidebar/TopBar, marketing pages, FullCalendar, jspdf, admin Core screens not yet built on mobile.

## Mandatory verification (every batch)

### Gate A — BEFORE new code

```bash
cd web && npm run build
# when mobile exists:
cd mobile/app && npx tsc --noEmit
```

### Gate B — AFTER code, BEFORE commit

```bash
cd web && npm run build
cd mobile/app && npx tsc --noEmit   # when mobile exists
rg -i "Affiliate [Pp]ortal|For Affiliate Member" web/ mobile/ packages/ --glob "*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}"
rg "PORTAL_META\s*=" web/ mobile/ --glob "*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}" | rg -v "shared-constants|SHARED_PORTAL"
```

Expected: 0 stale user-facing "Affiliate portal" strings; no duplicate `PORTAL_META` outside shared package.

## Verification Report (paste in every batch)

```
## Batch N Verification Report
Gate A: web build PASS/FAIL | mobile tsc PASS/FAIL/N/A
Gate B: web build PASS/FAIL | mobile tsc PASS/FAIL/N/A | naming grep PASS/FAIL
Defects fixed: ...
Blockers: ...
```

Do NOT start the next batch until all gates PASS.

## Portal naming (current)

| UI label | Key | Role |
|----------|-----|------|
| Core | `staff` | staff roles |
| Associate | `associate` | `associate` |
| My CA | `client` | `client` |
| Partner | `partner` | `partner` |

Legacy URL `?portal=affiliate` maps to `associate` via `normalizePortalSlug()`.
